<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="External_links">External links</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Source_protection&amp;action=edit&amp;section=40" title="Edit section: External links"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<ul><li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://ssrn.com/abstract=1706688">Silencing Sources: An International Survey of Protections and Threats to Journalists’ Sources</a>. Global survey of source protection laws by Privacy International, 2007.</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.echr.coe.int/NR/rdonlyres/0856B8A0-D3A1-47B4-B969-6250E84F9F3D/0/FICHES_Protection_des_sources_journalistiques_EN.pdf">ECtHR case law factsheet on the protection of journalistic sources</a></li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20120303080302/https://www.privacyinternational.org/article/model-brief-protection-journalists-sources">Model Brief on the Protection of Journalists' Sources</a> by Privacy International 2009. Creative Commons Non-Commercial Use</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.article19.org/pdfs/letters/sanoma-uitgevers-b.v.-v-the-netherlands.pdf">Amicus Curiae brief in <i>Sanoma Uitgevers B.V. v the Netherlands</i></a>, providing an overview of International and European domestic law on protection of sources - the <a href="/wiki/Open_Society_Justice_Initiative" class="mw-redirect" title="Open Society Justice Initiative">Open Society Justice Initiative</a>, the <a href="/wiki/Committee_to_Protect_Journalists" title="Committee to Protect Journalists">Committee to Protect Journalists</a>, the <a href="/wiki/Media_Legal_Defence_Initiative" class="mw-redirect" title="Media Legal Defence Initiative">Media Legal Defence Initiative</a>, <a href="/wiki/ARTICLE_19" class="mw-redirect" title="ARTICLE 19">ARTICLE 19</a>, and <a href="/wiki/The_Guardian" title="The Guardian">the Guardian</a> News and Media Limited, December 2009.</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://beschermjegegevens.nl/wp-content/uploads/InfoSec-for-Journalists-V1.3-1.pdf">Infosec for Investigative Journalists, version 2016</a> by Silkie Carlo and Arjen Kamphuis.</li></ul>
